## Fix Settings > Lakebase Objects showing "No objects owned by you"

**Root cause:** `graph_engine_lakebase_objects_result` filtered schemas with `WHERE nspowner = current_user`. In the deployed app, `current_user` is the SP (`95084ef9-...`). Bootstrap creates all schemas as the deploying human user (`benoit.cayla`), so the SP doesn't OWN any schema → empty result → "No objects owned by you in this database."

The graph schema `ontobricks_graph_demo2` (with `*__app` / `*_sync` companion tables) was invisible despite the SP having `USAGE` on it.

**Fix in `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`:**
- Widened the WHERE clause to `nspowner = current_user OR has_schema_privilege(current_user, nspname, 'USAGE')`.
- Added `'public'` to the exclusion list (system schema, no app objects).
- The frontend already strips the registry schema (`ontobricks_demo`) by name, so only the graph schema(s) and their tables/views appear.

**Verified via psql:** SP has USAGE on `ontobricks_demo` (registry, filtered by frontend), `ontobricks_graph_demo2` (graph — now visible), and `public` (now excluded).

**Modified files:**
- `src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py`
